('QsubWBPoVIU', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-035705', '10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-035705', 'To Gibberellins and Beyond! Surveying the Evolution of (Di)Terpenoid Metabolism: Video 1', 'Annual Reviews Extra', 'Video from the 2014 review by Jiachen Zi, Sibongile Mafu, and Reuben J. Peters, "To Gibberellins and Beyond! Surveying the Evolution of (Di)Terpenoid Metabolism," from the Annual Review of Plant Biology: http://www.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-035705?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=pp.65.zi&utm_campaign=suppvideo\n\nBicyclization and ring rearrangement reaction catalyzed by kaurene synthase.', '2014-01-22 21:57:19', 'biosynthesis, terpene synthases, cytochrome P450, phytoalexins, allelochemicals', NULL, NULL, 'UCG5VAYGeyQzOQ0CXSZOZEfw', '10', '290', '2', '0', '0', '0', 0, '2020-07-29 17:38:24'),
('ueMWQvpSNaY', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-040240', '10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-040240', 'The Cell Biology of Cellulose Synthesis: Video 1', 'Annual Reviews Extra', 'A video from the 2014 review by Heather E. McFarlane, Anett Dring, and Staffan Persson, "The Cell Biology of Cellulose Synthesis," from the Annual Review of Plant Biology: http://www.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-040240?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=pp.65.mcfarlane&utm_campaign=suppvideo\n\nGFP-CesA3 signal in the plasma membrane of Arabidopsis dark-grown hypocotyl cells. Small particles of GFP-CesA3 signal at the plasma membrane presumably represent cellulose synthase (CesA) complexes (CSCs) that probably include multiple copies of the GFP-tagged CesA3 subunit. These particles move at a constant speed along a linear trajectory as the CSC synthesizes cellulose. Individual particles appear, representing CSC deliveries to the membrane, and other particles eventually disappear from the plasma membrane, implying that the CSC may be recycled after some time. The scale bar represents 10 m, the time stamp shows minutes:seconds, and the video covers 12.5 min of imaging.', '2014-02-28 00:52:40', 'cell wall, extracellular matrix, plant growth and development, secretion, Arabidopsis thaliana, Cellulose (Chemical Compound)', NULL, NULL, 'UCG5VAYGeyQzOQ0CXSZOZEfw', '16', '2079', '4', '0', '0', '0', 0, '2020-07-29 17:38:24'),
('5KII94ffag0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-040240', '10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-040240', 'The Cell Biology of Cellulose Synthesis: Video 2', 'Annual Reviews Extra', 'A video from the 2014 review by Heather E. McFarlane, Anett Dring, and Staffan Persson, "The Cell Biology of Cellulose Synthesis," from the Annual Review of Plant Biology: http://www.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev-arplant-050213-040240?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=pp.65.mcfarlane&utm_campaign=suppvideo\n\nGFP-CesA3 signal in the Golgi apparatus of Arabidopsis dark-grown hypocotyl cells. Ring-shaped aggregations of GFP-CesA3 signal inside the cell represent cellulose synthases (CesAs) as they trafc through the Golgi apparatus. Golgi stacks undergo salutatory movement or rapid cytosolic streaming. The scale bar represents 10 m, the time stamp shows minutes:seconds, and the video covers 100 s of imaging.', '2014-02-28 00:54:32', 'cell wall, extracellular matrix, plant growth and development, secretion, Arabidopsis thaliana, Cellulose (Chemical Compound)', NULL, NULL, 'UCG5VAYGeyQzOQ0CXSZOZEfw', '11', '949', '1', '0', '0', '0', 0, '2020-07-29 17:38:24'),
