('VzTDilWrDvE', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1016/j.cub.2014.03.022', '10.1016/j.cub.2014.03.022', 'Insects with Female Penises Discovered, the Birth of a New Moon, and More!', 'IFLScience', 'This week on IFLS, a female insect develops a penis-like sex organ, the Kepler team discovers the most Earth-like planet YET, a meteorite explodes over Russia (again!), and much more!\n\nTo check out Elise\'s favorite science book, The Ancestor\'s Tale, and more, go to audible.com/IFLS for a FREE Audiobook-download when you sing up today! \n\nLearn More:\nEclipse: http://bit.ly/1mfdMJu\nMeteorite: http://bit.ly/1mmN6Xi\nPeggy: http://bit.ly/1inhVu9\nSexual organs: http://bit.ly/1eOQEC5\n original study: http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.cub.2014.03.022\nSpaceX launch: http://bit.ly/1jkGIf6\nEarth sized planet: http://bit.ly/1r35BQN\n\nJoin Elise each week to see the all the latest and greatest stories from the lighter side of science, including popular science, space, biology, nature, and more. Subscribe now!\n\nSubscribe Now! https://www.youtube.com/user/IFLScience\nIFLS on Facebook http://facebook.com/ifeakinglovescience\nElise on Twiiter http://twitter.com/elise_andrew', '2014-04-22 16:49:31', 'testtube, science, popular science, culture, labs, space, outer space, elise andrews, Facebook, scientists, dnews, new moon, peggy, NASA, meteorite, sexual organs, Earth sized planet, spacex launch rings, asteroid, dwarf, russian meteorite, russia meteor, spacex, Space-X, spacex falcon, blood moon, blood moon eclipse, I Fucking Love Science, IFLS, elise andrew, new mammal, discovery', NULL, NULL, 'UCvOTgnW7oj9ZWDd2y5TEApw', '233', '104650', '1781', '43', '119', '0', 0, '2020-07-29 17:58:03'),
('LfQ9CxKaQhc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1093/molbev/msu068', 'academic.oup.com/mbe/article/31/5/1173/996855', 'Contested Bones XX: Australopithecine feet, Some Gish chat & Bechly on biogeography', 'James Downard', 'Evolution Hour 58 is a busy one, with a special guest (God Free World) to reminisce on the creationist debating manner of the late Duane Gish.  There\'s more on Rupe & Sanford\'s CONTESTED BONES series of course, this time on the pitter patter of little Laeoti feet, and IDer Gunter Bechly going all Casey Luskin on disputing biogeography.\n\nSome links to chew on:\n\nPeter Schmid 2004 https://www.researchgate.net/publication/283311149_Functional_Interpretation_of_the_Laetoli_Footprints\n\nMatthew Bennett et al. 2009 http://www2.gwu.edu/~newsctr/newscenter/research/footprint/sciencemag.pdf newer 1.5 mya Kenyan footprints\n\nDavid Raichlen et al 2010 http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0009769 Laetoli bipedality\n\nRupe & Sanford did cite, but most selectively, Carl Ward et al 2011 http://groups.molbiosci.northwestern.edu/horvath/journClubArticles/JC_for_December%206,%202013.pdf on A. afarensis\' fourth metatarsal & how it continued to show they were a full committed biped\n\nRobin Crompton et al 2012 http://rsif.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/9/69/707 on the bipedality of the Laetoli prints\n\nKevin Hatala et al. 2016 http://rspb.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/283/1836/20160235 on the not quite human gate of those Laetoli footprints\n\nGunter Bechly https://evolutionnews.org/2018/06/rafting-stormy-waters-when-biogeography-contradicts-common-ancestry/\n\nIts interesting to compare some of his cited sources with how Bechly chose to spin them.\n\nNeil Cumberlidge et al. 2008 (ID groupie Richard Sternberg was a coauthor!) https://www.nmu.edu/sites/DrupalBiology/files/UserFiles/Files/Pre-Drupal/SiteSections/Faculty/Bios/Pubpdfs/Cumberlidge_etal_2008.pdf\n\nCumberlidge & Peter Ng 2009 https://www.researchgate.net/publication/279417433_Systematics_Evolution_and_Biogeography_of_Freshwater_Crabs\n\nLing Tsang et al. 2014 https://academic.oup.com/mbe/article/31/5/1173/996855 more on freshwater crabs\n\nAnd then theres the floating islands issue, where Alain Houle 1998 explicitly noted observed examples, which Bechly never discussed https://www.researchgate.net/publication/283868225_Floating_islands_A_mode_of_long-distance_dispersal_for_small_and_medium-sized_terrestrial_vertebrates\n\nBechly was in pure Gish selective quote mining mode when he trawled George Simpson 1940 http://people.wku.edu/charles.smith/biogeog/SIMP940B.htm misrepresenting the criticism he offered as Simpson was agreeing with it.\n\nAnd then there are the Australian spiders Sophie Harrison et al 2017 explored in http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0180139\n\nBechly didnt discuss either their data or offer his explanation for how the spiders got there.   Was God (sublimely indifferent to human suffering in Inquisitions, wars and Holocausts) taking a liking to materializing a certain tarantula in Australia?\n\nSome more of the ID dance on this, Uncommon Descent https://uncommondescent.com/evolution/shaking-the-bird-family-tree-african-type-bird-fossil-from-52-mya-found-in-north-america/ regarding Daniel Field & Allison Hsiang 2018 https://bmcevolbiol.biomedcentral.com/track/pdf/10.1186/s12862-018-1212-3\n\nAn Uncommon Descent sideswipe at Nick Matzke (but NOT linking to Matzkes paper directly, only the criticism on a subject whose details UD did not elaborate on, let alone explain within their own ID framework) https://uncommondescent.com/evolution/nick-matzkes-research-critiqued-in-journal-of-biogeography/\n\nMy TIP website is www.tortucan.wordpress.com stop by and say Hi!\n\nIf you want to give more than just a thumbs up to the work, there\'s a place for that: www.GoFundMe.com/dseego\n\nYou can get my tour de force Evolution Slam Dunk creationism squasher at https://www.amazon.com/dp/1540736296/ref=sr_1_2?ie=UTF8&qid=1481509663&sr=8-2&keywords=Evolution+slam+dunk', '2018-07-12 01:58:28', 'Christopher Rupe, Jon Sanford, Contested Bones book, Laetoli footprints, creationism, Intelligent Design, Peter Schmid, Matthew Bennett, David Raichlen, Carl Ward, Robin Crompton, Kevin Hatala, Gunter Bechly, Biogeography, Casey Luskin, Neil Cumberlidge, Peter Ng, Ling Tsang, Alain Houle, George Gaylord Simpson, Sophie Harrison, Australian spiders, Uncommon Descent website, Nick Matzke, Bird evolution, Daniel Field, Allison Hsiang, God Free World', NULL, 'en', 'UCRdnABwU9uUJw1k40LGYcQA', '5494', '222', '20', '1', '20', '0', 1, '2020-07-29 18:05:34'),
